            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>For the safety of the Imperator Hadrian Augustus, father of the fatherland, to Fortuna Redux. By decree of the council of 100, 
                    with public money, from ten pounds of silver for those carrying out the administration. When Publius Aburtennius Priscus and 
                    Publius Aburtennius Restitutus were quattuorviri.
                </p>
